page.title: 16SIDE WOOD
page.content: Side Wood can be found on the south side of Ennerdale Water.It is a complete contrast to the 3000 acres of forest that covers most of the upper valley because Side Wood is a superb example of the ancient Oak and Birch woodland that covered a large part of the Lake District thousands of years ago.This habitat supports a wide variety of species. Side Wood shows the sign of mans activites with evidence of charcoal burning and coppicing. The site has been awarded the status of a Site of Special Scientific Interest.
